# InnovaHack 2026 — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env.local (or just edit .env) and fill in your actual values.
# NEVER commit files containing real keys to version control.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Supabase Project URL
# Find in: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API → Project URL
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Supabase API Key
# Use ONE of the variable names below — the app accepts all of them.
#
# Recommended: use the anon/public key (safe to use in the browser).
# Find in: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API → anon / public
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Standard name (recommended)
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key-here

# Alternative name — used by some Supabase starter templates
# VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_DEFAULT_KEY=your-anon-public-key-here

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# IMPORTANT NOTES
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Only set ONE of the key variables above. If both are set,
#    VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY takes priority.
#
# 2. NEVER use the service_role key here — it bypasses all
#    Row Level Security and should only be used server-side.
#
# 3. After creating/editing this file, restart the dev server:
#      npm run dev
#
# 4. For Vercel deployment, add these same variables in:
#    Vercel Dashboard → Your Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#
# 5. See supabase/INSTRUCTIONS.md for full setup guide.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
